verses.text:
Death comes on with reckless footstep, To the hall and hut;
Think you death will tarry knocking Where the door is shut?
Jesus waiteth, waiteth, waiteth, But thy door is fast;
Grieveth that His love must leave thee, Leave thee for the last.

By and by the night of weeping Shall be lost in day;
By and by the chains of darkness Shall be rent away;
But 'twill be too late, too late, When the dawn appears,
For the Master will not linger When the night is o'er.
